OL,3,GNEWSCBBC Northern Ireland politics
OL,4,Cprogramme moves to multi-platform
OL,5,Cstudio
OL,6,
OL,7,FBBC Northern Ireland's Sunday morning
OL,8,Fpolitics programme, Sunday Politics,
OL,9,Fwas broadcast from its new
OL,10,Fmulti-platform studio for the first
OL,11,Ftime this morning.
OL,13,FThe Studio 5 facility at BBC
OL,14,FBroadcasting House in Belfast allows
OL,15,Fthe programme to be produced by a
OL,16,Fsmaller production team.
OL,18,FThe programme is also now broadcast
OL,19,Flive on BBC Radio Ulster, BBC Radio
OL,20,FFoyle and BBC Sounds, as well as on its
OL,21,Ftraditional home on BBC One Northern
OL,22,FIreland and BBC iPlayer.
OL,23,EPub: 19-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,144,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14302
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F143A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/4
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWSCBBC Northern Ireland politics
OL,4,Cprogramme moves to multi-platform
OL,5,Cstudio
OL,6,
OL,7,FPresenter Mark Carruthers, who has
OL,8,Fpresented the programme since 2012,
OL,9,Fsaid: "It's going to be an awful lot
OL,10,Feasier for people to watch or listen to
OL,11,Fthis programme, for example, on their
OL,12,Fphones or on their tablets.
OL,14,F"Moving to the new studio allows us to
OL,15,Fincrease the reach of Sunday Politics."
OL,17,F"The whole broadcast landscape is
OL,18,Fchanging and changing so dramatically,"
OL,19,Fhe said.
OL,23,EPub: 19-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,144,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14303
SC,0003
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F143A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/4
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWSCBBC Northern Ireland politics
OL,4,Cprogramme moves to multi-platform
OL,5,Cstudio
OL,6,
OL,7,F"We have to think about our audience
OL,8,Ffirst and foremost, and the way people
OL,9,Fconsume news, the way people consume
OL,10,Fcurrent affairs is changing."
OL,12,FHe added: "It's really important for us
OL,13,Fto be getting a live politics
OL,14,Fdiscussion programme out on the BBC
OL,15,FRadio Ulster schedule again on a Sunday
OL,16,Fmorning."
OL,18,FSenior news editor Gwyneth Jones said
OL,19,Fit was exciting to be switching to a
OL,20,Fmulti-platform studio, adding that the
OL,21,Fmedia landscape is changing.
OL,23,EPub: 19-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,144,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14304
SC,0004
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F143A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/4
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWSCBBC Northern Ireland politics
OL,4,Cprogramme moves to multi-platform
OL,5,Cstudio
OL,6,
OL,7,F"I think there's a realisation, and
OL,8,Fthere has been for some time, that we
OL,9,Fneed to go where our audiences are, so
OL,10,Fthat is no longer only on a linear
OL,11,Fbroadcast telly format," she said.
OL,13,F"We are still delivering the same
OL,14,Ftrusted live political journalism where
OL,15,Fpublic figures are held to account and
OL,16,Fwhere their decisions are scrutinised,
OL,17,Fas we've always done, but we are
OL,18,Fbringing that to a much wider
OL,19,Faudience."
OL,23,EPub: 19-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
